-- int_deduped_channels.sql
```sql
-- Dedupe customer channels to one per customer
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }}
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    channel
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- int_customer_revenue.sql
```sql
-- Join transactions with customers and deduped channels
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        t.transaction_id,
        t.customer_id,
        t.store_id,
        t.amount,
        t.transaction_date,
        COALESCE(dc.channel, '(unknown)') AS channel
    FROM {{ ref('stg_transactions') }} t
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_channels') }} dc
        ON dc.customer_id = t.customer_id
)
SELECT
    transaction_id,
    customer_id,
    store_id,
    amount,
    transaction_date,
    channel
FROM source
```

-- fct_revenue_by_channel_city.sql
```sql
-- Customer revenue by attribution channel and city
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        cr.channel,
        COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)') AS city,
        cr.amount,
        cr.transaction_id,
        cr.customer_id
    FROM {{ ref('int_customer_revenue') }} cr
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_stores') }} s
        ON s.store_id = cr.store_id
)
SELECT
    channel,
    city,
    SUM(amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(transaction_id) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM source
GROUP BY
    channel,
    city
